 @{b}About...@{ub}
     Opens a little info requester.
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-?

 @{b}About MUI...@{ub}
     Some infos on MUI.

 @{b}Iconify@{ub}
     Closes all windows and sends CallMan to sleep.
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-i

 @{b}Quit@{ub}
     Quits the program.
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-q



 @{b}Preferences...@{ub}
     Opens the @{" prefernces window " link "Usage_Prefs"}.
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-p

 @{b}Edit rates files...@{ub}
     Opens a window, where you can @{" edit the rates files " link "Usage_PrefsRates"}.
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-r

 @{b}MUI...@{ub}
     Starts the MUI prefs.
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-m

 @{b}Cleanup logfile...@{ub}
     This menu item removes all 'aborted' phone calls (i.e. calls with an
     unknown duration) from the logfile. You will be prompted whether you
     really would like to perform this operation. After cleaning up CallMan
     tells you about the number of removed entries.
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-l

 @{b}TelephoneBill window@{ub}
     Switch to @{" TelephoneBill mode " link "Usage_TB"}, a smaller window including
     automatic calculation of the total phone and modem costs at a user definable
     interval.
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-t

 @{b}Log call without dialling...@{ub}
     Opens the @{" Call window " link "Usage_Call"} without actually dialling the active
     phonenumber. Useful whenever you have "accidentally" dialled by hand but
     still wanrt to log the call. :)
     Shortcut: RAMIGA-w



 @{b}Import...@{ub}
     @{" ASCII " link "Usage_Import_ASCII"}

 @{b}Show all entries@{ub}
     When active, CallMan will display all entries (including "invisible" ones)
     in the @{" main window " link "Usage_Main"} database list.

 @{b}Edit database categories@{ub}
     Opens the @{" database category window " link "Usage_Category"}.

@EndNode


