@Node "Usage_Main" "Main window"

  The main window is divided into two logical groups.


  The upper group contains a list, displaying the names
  of the persons saved in the database, and below it four
  gadgets, used to manipulate the entries. Using the
  category popupgadget you can limit the displayed entries
  to any of the user-definable @{" categories " link "Usage_Category"}.
  The list itself is sorted according to the setting in the
  @{" preferences window " link "Prefs_CM"}.
  The list has its own popup menu allowing for a quick
  access to the "edit" and "dial" options as well as adding
  the active entry to the "Dial" button's popup menu (see
  below).

  @{"    New     " link "Main_New"}@{"    Edit    " link "Main_Edit"}@{"   Delete   " link "Main_Delete"}@{"    Save    " link "Main_Save"}



  The lower Group consists of two textgadgets, displaying
  name and phonenumber of the active entry. Below there
  are four gadgets:

  @{"         Dial        " link "Main_Dial"   }  @{"      Quickdial      " link "Main_QuickDial"}

  @{"   Analyze logfile   " link "Main_Analyze"}  @{"        Quit         " link "Main_Quit"     }

  The "Dial" button has its own popup menu to which
  you can assign up to four database entries (using
  the menu as a REAL quickdial option).

@EndNode

@Node "Main_New" "Main window: New"

  Appends a new entry to the database. Using the @{" edit window " link "Usage_Edit"} you
  can enter the new record.

@EndNode

@Node "Main_Edit" "Main window: Edit"

  Using the @{" edit window " link "Usage_Edit"} you can edit the data of the active
  entry.

@EndNode

@Node "Main_Delete" "Main window: Delete"

  Removed the active entry from the database.

  WARNING: There is NO security check! As soon as you press the
           'Delete' button, the entry will be removed.

@EndNode

@Node "Main_Save" "Main window: Save"

  Saves the database to the directory specified in the
  @{" prefs window " link "Usage_Prefs"}.

@EndNode

@Node "Main_Dial" "Main window: Dial"

  Dials the phonenumber of the active entry and opens the @{" call window " link "Usage_Call"}.

  Placing the mouse pointer over the gadget and pressing the right mouse
  button will open the gadget's own popup menu. Selecting any of the four
  entries will start dialling up the according person.

@EndNode

@Node "Main_QuickDial" "Main window: Quickdial"

  'Quickdial' lets you dial a phonenumber that is not included in the
  database. You can enter the required data in the @{" quickdial window " link "Usage_QuickDial"}.

@EndNode

@Node "Main_Analyze" "Main window: Analyze logfile"

  Opens the @{" analyze window " link "Usage_Analyze"}.

@EndNode

@Node "Main_Quit" "Main window: Quit"

  Quits the program.

  WARNING: There is no confirmation whether you really want to quit the
           program and the database is NOT saved on exit!

@EndNode


@Node "Usage_TB" "TelephoneBill window"

  When switching to 'TelephoneBill' mode the main window is replaced by
  the smaller 'TelephoneBill' window, consisting of only four textgadgets:

  - the upper textgadget displays the calculating timespan.

  - the next textgadget displays the phone costs.

  - the textgadget in the middle shows the modem costs.

  - the lower textgadget displays the total costs of phone and modem costs.
    Additionally you can tell the program to add a basic charge to the total
    costs. See @{" prefs window " link "Usage_Prefs"} on how to set this option and set
    the basic charge.

  See @{" prefs window " link "Usage_Prefs"} on how to set the calculating
  timespan as well as the calculating interval.

  If you are online during calculation of the modem costs an '(online)' is
  appended to the modem costs.

  Whenever during calculation CallMan encounters a phonenumber not present in
  the database, the default region set in the @{" prefs window " link "Usage_Prefs"} is used
  as the region for this number. In this case the calculated costs might
  differ from the actual value and the corresponding textgadget is marked
  with an asterisk '*'.

  If any of the logfiles couldn't get loaded you will either see 'no logfile'
  (CallMan logfile missing) or an '!' (modem logfile missing) appended to the
  costs.

  In case of an error during calculation (phonenumber not present in database
  or without region assigned) an @{" error window " link "Usage_TBError"} will pop up
  (if the corresponding option is set in the @{" prefs window " link "Usage_Prefs"}).

@EndNode

@Node "Usage_TBError" "TelephoneBill error window"

  This small error window contains two lists and a "Continue" button to close
  the window again.

  The upper list displays all phonenumbers that are not present in the
  database. To calculate the costs the program will use the default region
  set in the @{" prefs window " link "Usage_Prefs"} as the region for these
  unknown numbers. The actual costs might therefore differ from the
  calculated value.
  Using the buttons "Add active to database" and "Add all to database" you
  can add the active number or all numbers to the database.

  The lower list shows all phonenumbers that don't have a region assigned.
  All these numbers will not be considered when calculating the costs. If
  there are any numbers in this list, you can be sure the calculated costs
  are NOT accurate.

@EndNode


@Node "Usage_Edit" "Edit window"

  @{" Basics " link "Usage_Edit_Basics"} @{" Communication " link "Usage_Edit_Comm"} @{" Miscellaneous " link "Usage_Edit_Misc"} @{" Multimedia files " link "Usage_Edit_Multimedia"}  @{" Categories " link "Usage_Edit_Categories"}

