   can display these files by double-clicking on them or using
   the "show" button
 - time span in "Analyze" window now defaults to the time span
   set in the preferences
 - "TelephoneBill" window now also displays time span
 - modem statistics messed up conversation partners; fixed
 - database entries with at least one number without region
   can now optionally be displayed in italics
 - added MICRODOT-1 scanner/analyzer
 - error window: adding a single unknown number to the database
   without actually selecting a number from the list would
   create a nonsense database entry; fixed
 - removed textfield 'category' from database
 - added global category list to the database
 - added individual category settings for each database entry
 - added option to select displayed database entries by
   category
 - reworked dial code
 - added explicit 'modem priority' switch to preferences
 - dialling can now be aborted by pressing ESC or clicking
   on the dial window's close gadget; note: this only works
   before the actual modem dialling has begun!
 - fixed bug while initializing database category window
 - fixed stupid bug in dial code that would return an error whenever
   there was no modem-init string specified
 - added (experimental) GPFax scanner
 - extended modem statistics:
   you can now list the number of calls for each weekday
   and for all hours of the day separately
 - added preferences switch to enable/disable modem statistics
 - added simple security checks to all scanner modules; should
   prevent scanning logfiles with the wrong scanner
 - TRAPDOOR scanner would crash on logfiles containing
   'PhoneBill' entries; fixed
 - TRAPDOOR scanner ignored all 'Calling' entries; fixed
 - hopefully fixed the "switching to TB mode" bug
 - added AREXX commands:
   NUMBEROFENTRIES (number of total database entries)
   GETENTRY entrynumber destvar (fill destvar with entry 'entrynumber')
 - added "CallMan-Export.rexx" export script
 - analyze window: adding a single unknown number to the database
   without actually selecting a number from the list would
   create a nonsense database entry; fixed
 - moved conversation partner's comment to separate column in modem
   statistic window
 - arexx command GETENTRY did some memory trashing when dealing
   with database entries without phonenumbers & email addresses; fixed
 - reworking of dial code screwed up "log without dialling" and
   "quickdial"; fixed
 - MIAMI scanner choked on PhoneBill entries; fixed
 - GPFax scanner sometimes screwed up the call's date; fixed
 - added AREXX command:
   DIAL entrynumber (dialup 'entrynumber')
 - added two new switches to rates files:
   switch 1: calculate costs using "seconds/unit" or "costs/second"
