   window would account "2 units due" (instead of only 1 unit); fixed
 - "cancelling" the rates window could sometimes crash CallMan: fixed
 - fixed a serious "enter dates in CallMan" bug
 - "log call without dialling" without an active database entry would
   confuse CallMan; fixed
 - fixed a few bugs in the "call in progress" cost calculation code
 - re-coded rates window code
 - enforcer hit in rates window on opening the file requester; fixed
 - fixed some more lame "date" bugs in rates and logfile window
 - added "CallMan" scanner module to list of "external" scanners
 - new AREXX commands:
   LOGWITHOUTDIALLING entrynumber hidden
                      (if application is iconified and hidden is set
                       to 1, application will not be uniconified)
   CONVERSATIONSTART
   CONVERSATIONEND
   CONVERSATIONABORT
 - added "w" to valid phone number characters; this should fix the
   problem with numbers not being recognized although they have
   successfully been added to the database
 - hitting "cancel" in "call in progress" window during suffix 2
   delay wouldn't properly close serial device; fixed
 - sometimes during dialling CallMan would pop up an infinite number
   of (error) requesters and then crash; fixed
 - crash in case of an error during dialling; fixed
 - "Perform calculation for this month" would always calculate
   the costs ranging from the first day of the current month
   to the last day of the year; fixed
 - logfile window never used current month as default with
   "Perform calculation for this month" set in preferences; fixed
 - extended MultiTerm scanner to properly deal with MT 5.0
   logfiles
 - fixed a bug in the dialling code that could cause some unmotivated
   "init" or "modem" errors

@EndNode


